\section*{X Windows}
\label{x-windows}

X-Windows, otherwise known as just \emph{X}, is the Unix version of the well-known Windows/Mouse Graphical User Interface.
First developed at Parc-Xerox\raisebox{.5em}[0em]{\scriptsize\hyperlink{id5}{1}} the concept of using
overlapping windows, and a 'mouse' is often seen as the \emph{only} way to interact with a computer.

Of course the unix tradition is for a command line interface - that of typing in commands to a shell,
and is a more powerful way to interact in almost all cases{\color{red}\bfseries{}{[}{\#}{]}{\_}} . X-windows is of course the comic book variant of the command line
that is the normal world of books. However at times comics can replace normal books.


